Class GameData

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • data.GameData

  • public class GameData
extends java.util.Observable
    GameData is the class that will be used to keep track of the important game information, including the number of weeks passed, the lists of all/active contestants, and the number of weeks remaining.
    Author:
    Graem Littleton, Ramesh Raj, Justin McDonald, Jonathan Demelo, Kevin Brightwell

    • Constructor Detail

      • GameData

        public GameData(int numInitialContestants)
        Constructor method that takes a set number of contestants. Will not proceed if numInitialContestants is NOT between 6 and 15, inclusive. Sets number of weeks passed to 0 and weeks remaining to number of contestants - 3.
        Parameters:
        numInitialContestants - number of contestants to be in game
